page.title: 07The river Hundred, Henstead
page.content: The river Hundred has no real commerce attached to it, not even fishing for eels. The occasional school boy can be seen fishing for pike as the river goes under the A12. During the past 5 years the river has been under strict coypu control. The main vegetation is; water lilies, water buttercups, water forget-me-nots, water mint, water crowfoot, water irises, marsh willowherb, rushes, horsetails, marsh marigold, sedges, bur-reed, nettles and plantain. Hawthorn hedgerows with small outcrops of young beeches run along the edge of the boggy pasture land. Visible creatures are; flarworms, freshwater shrimps, bristleworms, tubiflex, leeches, water fleas, may flies, water boatmen, water beetles, water mites, water spiders, water snails, caddis fly and larvae.
